,Recommended,230310,7533870,"Posted: 31 October, 2013",all,Fogg,"First Impressions:If you like dungeon crawlers this worth the $5 sale price. It will inevitably be F2P, but the starter items you get with the purchase will hold you over for quite a while. The art style reminds me of Japanese paintings, the traditional sounding music fits the atmosphere perfectly, and the pacing has been good.I was surprised to hear that the game has a lot in common with Bastion, but after seeing how they did the town I can see it.At this point in early access the game is designed to start sending you back to the earlier areas at higher difficulties to allow you to grind xp and items. Enemy variety has been good for the early part of the game, but the maps appear to be static. I have always felt that randomized areas help give dungeon crawlers longevity so it'll be interesting to see what they do.I suggest starting with the Fortitude character, currency is shared as well as the stash so if you decide to have multiple characters it's easy to pass stuff between them.It also appears that you can summon an ally, even if offline, and they will get rewards for it. Very cool concept."
